  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-a432bfbad0d1",
  "content": ": `cargo check`\nExpected: compiles with no errors\n\n**Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-common/src/config.rs crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_types.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): RagConfig in corvia-common — [rag] section with defaults\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: GenerationEngine Trait\n\nAdd the `GenerationEngine` trait to `traits.rs`. This is the generation stage interface (D63).\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/traits.rs`\n- Modify: `crates/corvia-kernel/src/rag_types.rs` (import)\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing test**\n\nAdd to the bottom of `crates/corvia-kernel/src/traits.rs` (create a `#[cfg(test)]` module if none exists):\n\n```rust\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod tests {\n    use super::*;\n\n    struct MockGenerator;\n    #[async_trait]\n    impl GenerationEngine for MockGenerator {\n        fn name(&self) -> &str { \"mock\" }\n        async fn generate(\n            &self,\n            _system_prompt: &str,\n            user_message: &str,\n        ) -> corvia_common::errors::Result<crate::rag_types::GenerationResult> {\n            Ok(crate::rag_types::GenerationResult {\n                text: format!(\"Answer to: {user_message}\"),\n                model: \"mock-model\".into(),\n                input_tokens: user_message.len() / 4,\n                output_tokens: 10,\n            })\n        }\n        fn context_window(&self) -> usize { 4096 }\n    }\n\n    #[tokio::test]\n    async fn test_generation_engine_mock() {\n        let gen = MockGenerator;\n        assert_eq!(gen.name(), \"mock\");\n        assert_eq!(gen.context_window(), 4096);\n        let result = gen.generate(\"system\", \"What is auth?\").await.unwrap();\n        assert_eq!(result.text, \"Answer to: What is auth?\");\n        assert_eq!(result.model, \"mock-model\");\n    }\n}",
